KwaZulu-Natal (KZN) Tourism says the province is expected to rake in an estimated R300m this weekend as over 40 000 people attend the Vodacom Durban July – as well as it’s world famous after-parties. Those attending the showcase did not disappoint in showing off their glamorous outfits while punters bet on their favourite horses. KZN Tourism CEO Phindile Makwakwa says the Durban July has also brought a major boost to township tourism. [Watch] Glitz and glamour at Durban July 